Lyft said it is testing monthly subscription plans for active users, The Verge reported. The ride-hailing company will target its monthly subscriptions at users who spend up to $450 per month on the service. Lyft CEO Logan Green said the company would offer a selection of subscription packages, including: These packages would cover rides which cost up to $15. “We are going to move the entire industry from one based on ownership to one based on subscription,” said Green.